@chapter How to invoke @code{radctl}.
@cindex radctl, invocation

Radctl understands following command line options:

@table @code
@item -d DIR
@itemx --directory DIR
Specifies the directory where client configuration files reside
@ref{Client Overview}.

@item -s HOST
@itemx --server HOST
Specifies the name of the server to connect to. @emph{Please note} that
this is not a domain name, but rather the name under which server is
listed in @file{client.shadow} file @ref{client.shadow}.

@item -u USERNAME
@itemx --user USERNAME 
Specifies the username. If started without this option, @code{radctl}
will prompt for the username.

@item -p PASSWORD
@itemx --password PASSWORD
Specifies the password to be used while connecting to the server. If
started without this option, @code{radctl} will prompt user for the
password.

@item -v
@itemx --verbose
Enable verbose mode. In verbose mode all conversation with the
Radius server is echoed on stderr.

@item -?
@itemx --help
Display short usage help and exit.
@end table

