@node Radctl.sh, Builddbm, Radctl, Top
@chapter Radctl.sh
@pindex radctl.sh

The @code{radctl.sh} utility provides the alternative way to communicate
with the radius server. It uses the signal mechanism in order to do so.
It is invoked as:

@example
radctl.sh @var{command}
@end example

The valid @var{command}s are as follows:

@table @code

@item start
If @code{radiusd} is not running already, it is started. The
rest of the command line arguments is passed as command line to the
server.

@item stop
Stops running @code{radiusd}.

@item restart
Stops the server and then starts it again. The rest of the arguments
is passed as command line to the server.

@item reload
Causes running @code{radiusd} server to re-read its configuration files.

@item dumpdb
Tells @code{radiusd} to dump its user hash table into the file
@file{/var/log/radius.parse}. This can be used for debugging the
configuration files.

@item status
@code{radiusd} reports its memory usage statistics. The information is
logged under @code{Info} log level.

@item which
Reports the information about running copy of @code{radiusd}.

@end table

